My grandmother considered herself well-bred, and she never used "profanity." It's for no-good plebes, she used to say. However, she always talked down to people and treated them like dirt. She may never have uttered "crude" words, but she was one of the rudest people I have ever known.

The whole concept of vulgarity is largely elitist. The Latin etymology of vulgarity refers to things related to the common person. Shunning "crude" language is one of the tools of discrimination.

